# =========================================================
# Trivy ignore list — ACCEPTED risks, with justification.
# Format: AVD/AWS rule ID per line. Reviewed and accepted for the dev env.
# =========================================================

# Public EKS API endpoint + open CIDR.
# JUSTIFICATION: CI/CD runs Terraform + helm/kubectl from GitHub-HOSTED runners,
# whose IPs are dynamic, so the API server must be publicly reachable.
# Mitigations: restrict via var.cluster_public_access_cidrs, EKS RBAC/Access
# Entries, audit logging enabled. For prod: private endpoint + self-hosted
# runners (or a bastion) and remove these ignores.
AVD-AWS-0040
AVD-AWS-0041

# Unrestricted egress (0.0.0.0/0) on cluster/node/rds/efs security groups.
# JUSTIFICATION: worker nodes need outbound to pull images (ECR/registries),
# reach AWS APIs (STS/EC2/EKS), and CoreDNS. Egress-all is standard for EKS
# nodes; ingress is tightly restricted. Low risk.
AVD-AWS-0104

# S3 bucket not using a customer-managed KMS key.
# JUSTIFICATION: applies to the ALB access-logs bucket — AWS ELB access-log
# delivery ONLY supports SSE-S3 (AES256), NOT SSE-KMS/CMK. The Loki and
# bootstrap buckets DO use customer-managed keys.
AVD-AWS-0132

# Short-form IDs (matches Trivy table output), in case the runner uses them.
AWS-0040
AWS-0041
AWS-0104
AWS-0132

